NEXT STEPS:
1. Read rocm_attn_out_low_q8_wmma_wide_i8_kernel (ds4_rocm.c line 4258).
   Identify the lane-redundant reads: lanes L and L+16 in a WMMA wave32
   tile share the same A-matrix row (wqs) and the same B-matrix token
   (xqsa / xqsb).  Currently each lane issues its own global load — 6x
   redundancy in VMEM instructions per K-block.
2. Add rocm_attn_out_low_q8_wmma_wide_i8_lds_kernel.  Per K-block (32-byte
   K-step):
   - Lanes 0..15 cooperatively load wqs[0..31] for their row into LDS
     (16 rows x 32 bytes = 512 bytes weight LDS).
   - Lanes 16..31 cooperatively load xqsa[0..31] + xqsb[0..31] for their
     token into LDS (16 tokens x 64 bytes = 1024 bytes activation LDS).
   - __syncthreads (free in single-wave block but conceptually correct).
   - All 32 lanes read from LDS for the WMMA inputs.
   Pack the scales (w_scale, xa_scale, xb_scale) into LDS too — 16 rows
   x 6 bytes = 96 bytes scale LDS.  Total LDS: ~1.6 KiB per block.
3. Env-gate via DS4_ROCM_ATTN_OUT_LDS.  Default opt-in initially.
4. Bench: 184-tok prefill, 3 runs each.  Compare to current default.

